ref:Method.name: parseInt
ref:Method.description: Parses a string argument and returns an integer of the specified radix or base

ref:Method.name: parseFloat
ref:Method.description: Parses a string argument and returns a floating point number

ref:Method.name: decodeURI
ref:Method.description: Decodes a Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) previously created by encodeURI or by a similar routine.

ref:Method.name: decodeURIComponent
ref:Method.description: Decodes a Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) component previously created by encodeURIComponent or by a similar routine.

ref:Method.name: encodeURI
ref:Method.description: Encodes a Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) by replacing each instance of certain characters by one, two, three, or four escape sequences representing the UTF-8 encoding of the character (will only be four escape sequences for characters composed of two 'surrogate' characters).

ref:Method.name: encodeURIComponent
ref:Method.description: Encodes a Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) component by replacing each instance of certain characters by one, two, three, or four escape sequences representing the UTF-8 encoding of the character (will only be four escape sequences for characters composed of two 'surrogate' characters).

ref:Method.name: eval
ref:Method.description: Evaluates a string of JavaScript code without reference to a particular object.

ref:Method.name: escape
ref:Method.description: Encodes a string, so it can be transmitted across any network to any computer that supports ASCII characters.

ref:Method.name: unescape
ref:Method.description: Decodes an encoded string (encoded with escape).

ref:Method.name: isFinite
ref:Method.description: Evaluates an argument to determine whether it is a finite number.

ref:Method.name: isNaN
ref:Method.description: Evaluates an argument to determine if it is not a number.
